##
##  description.vm - this velocity script is executed to render the widget extended tooltip
##

The Widget renders a <b><i>Coverage/Traceability Table</b></i> for the defined set of Work Items. 
Each line indicates that the Work Item is either <i>Not Covered</i>, <i>Covered</i> or <i>Covered with an unresolved Item</i> 
linked to the Work Item that covers it.

<ul>
	<li>
		Main set of Work Items is defined using <b>Scope</b>, Work Item <b>Type</b> and <b>Query</b> parameters, the Work Items can be ordered using <b>Sort By</b> parameter.
	</li>
	<li>
		Linked Work Items that are covering the defined Main Work Items are configured using <b>Linked Item Type(s)</b> and <b>Linked Item -> Main Item Link Role(s)</b> parameters.
	</li>
	<li>
		The list of rendered linked Work Items can be filtered so it <i><b>displays</b> All found Work Items</i>, 
		<i>Problematic Work Items only</i> (Not Covered or Covered with at least one unresolved 2nd level Item) 
		or <i><b>hides</b> the Covered Work Items</i> 
		or the <i>Not Covered Work Items</i>, 
		all using the <b>Filter Linked Items By Coverage</b> parameter.
	</li>
	<li>
		Items further linked to the Linked Items are configured using <b>2nd Level Linked Item Type(s)</b> and 
		<b>2nd Level Linked Item -> Linked Item Link Role(s)</b> parameters.
	</li>
	<li>
		Work Item fields can be rendered for each displayed Work Item. This feature can be configured using the <b>Render Following Main/Linked/2nd Level Linked Work Item Fields</b> parameter. 
		The style of rendering can be further adjusted using Advanced tab - <b>Show Labels for WI Fields</b> and <b>Use Compact Mode for WI Fields</b> parameters.
	</li>	
	<li>
		Fields displayed on the Work Item Sidebar for all three levels of Work Items can be separately configured using <b>Main</b>, <b>Linked</b> and <b>2nd Level Linked</b> Work Item Properties Sidebar Fields parameters.
	</li>
	<li>
		The list can be configured so it collapses the set of linked Work Items if their count exceeds the number set in <b>Advanced - Collapse from Number of Linked Items</b> parameter.
	</li>
	<li>
		Titles of all columns can be specified in the Advanced tab using <b>Main Item</b>, <b>Linked Item</b> and <b>2nd Level Linked Item</b> Column Title parameters.
	</li>
</ul>
